text: The name Mitch was used once in the Atlantic Ocean. * Hurricane Mitch (1998) - A catastrophic Category 5 hurricane in the Caribbean Sea, which caused more than a 11,000 fatalities in Central America. The name was retired after the 1998 season, and was replaced by Matthew for the 2004 season. The name Mitchell was used for one tropical cyclone in the Australian region: * Cyclone Mitchell (2013) - A Category 1 cyclone in the Australian scale that didn't affect land.
